# 📍 Day 23 — Athena & Redshift

## 🎯 Objective

Understand analytics and data warehousing services in AWS.

---

## 📊 Amazon Athena

### 📌 What is Athena?

* Serverless query service
* Query data directly from S3 using SQL

---

### 📌 Key Features

* No infrastructure management
* Pay per query
* Works well with S3 data lakes

---

## 🏢 Amazon Redshift

### 📌 What is Redshift?

* Fully managed data warehouse
* Designed for large-scale analytics

---

### 📌 Key Features

* High-performance querying
* Columnar storage
* Optimized for analytics workloads

---

## ⚖️ Athena vs Redshift

| Feature        | Athena           | Redshift                 |
| -------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------ |
| Type           | Serverless Query | Data Warehouse           |
| Storage        | S3               | Internal cluster storage |
| Best For       | Ad-hoc queries   | Large-scale analytics    |
| Infrastructure | No management    | Managed cluster          |

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* Athena is ideal for querying S3 data directly
* Redshift is optimized for enterprise analytics
* Data architecture depends on query patterns & scale

---

